ipsecMIB.name: ipsecMIB
ipsecMIB.contactinfo: Tivoli Systems Research Triangle Park, NC Cisco Systems San Jose, CA
ipsecMIB.description: This is the MIB Module for objects to manage the IP Security Protocol.

IPSIpAddress.name: IPSIpAddress
IPSIpAddress.description: An IP V4 or V6 Address.

IkePeerType.name: IkePeerType
IkePeerType.description: The type of ipsec Phase-1 IKE peer identity. The IKE peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

IkeNegoMode.name: IkeNegoMode
IkeNegoMode.description: The ipsec Phase-1 IKE negotiation mode.

IkeHashAlgo.name: IkeHashAlgo
IkeHashAlgo.description: The hash algorithm used in ipsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

IkeAuthMethod.name: IkeAuthMethod
IkeAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used in ipsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

DiffHellmanGrp.name: DiffHellmanGrp
DiffHellmanGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used in negotiations.

KeyType.name: KeyType
KeyType.description: The type of key used by an ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

EncapMode.name: EncapMode
EncapMode.description: The encapsulation mode used by an ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

EncryptAlgo.name: EncryptAlgo
EncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used in negotiations.

AuthAlgo.name: AuthAlgo
AuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by a security association of an ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

CompAlgo.name: CompAlgo
CompAlgo.description: The compression algorithm used by a security association of an ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

EndPtType.name: EndPtType
EndPtType.description: The type of identity use to specify an ipsec End Point.

TunnelStatus.name: TunnelStatus
TunnelStatus.description: The status of a Tunnel. Objects of this type may be used to bring the tunnel down by setting value of this object to destroy(2). Objects of this type cannot be used to create a Tunnel.

TrapStatus.name: TrapStatus
TrapStatus.description: The administrative status for sending a TRAP.

ipsecMibLevel.name: ipsecMibLevel
ipsecMibLevel.description: The level of the ipsec MIB.

ikeGlobalPreviousTunnels.name: ikeGlobalPreviousTunnels
ikeGlobalPreviousTunnels.description: The total number of previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInOctets.name: ikeGlobalInOctets
ikeGlobalInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInPkts.name: ikeGlobalInPkts
ikeGlobalInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInDropPkts.name: ikeGlobalInDropPkts
ikeGlobalInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets which were dropped during receive processing by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInNotifys.name: ikeGlobalInNotifys
ikeGlobalInNotifys.description: The total number of notifys received by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInP2Exchgs.name: ikeGlobalInP2Exchgs
ikeGlobalInP2Exchgs.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges received by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInP2ExchgInvalids.name: ikeGlobalInP2ExchgInvalids
ikeGlobalInP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges which were received and found to be invalid by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInP2ExchgRejects.name: ikeGlobalInP2ExchgRejects
ikeGlobalInP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges which were received and rejected by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInP2SaDelRequests.name: ikeGlobalInP2SaDelRequests
ikeGlobalInP2SaDelRequests.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 security association delete requests received by all currently and previously active and ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalOutOctets.name: ikeGlobalOutOctets
ikeGlobalOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by all currently and previously active and ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalOutPkts.name: ikeGlobalOutPkts
ikeGlobalOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by all currently and previously active and ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalOutDropPkts.name: ikeGlobalOutDropPkts
ikeGlobalOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets which were dropped during send processing by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalOutNotifys.name: ikeGlobalOutNotifys
ikeGlobalOutNotifys.description: The total number of notifys sent by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalOutP2Exchgs.name: ikeGlobalOutP2Exchgs
ikeGlobalOutP2Exchgs.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges which were sent by all currently and previously active and ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalOutP2ExchgInvalids.name: ikeGlobalOutP2ExchgInvalids
ikeGlobalOutP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges which were sent and found to be invalid by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalOutP2ExchgRejects.name: ikeGlobalOutP2ExchgRejects
ikeGlobalOutP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges which were sent and rejected by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalOutP2SaDelRequests.name: ikeGlobalOutP2SaDelRequests
ikeGlobalOutP2SaDelRequests.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 security association delete requests sent by all currently and previously active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalInitTunnels.name: ikeGlobalInitTunnels
ikeGlobalInitTunnels.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels which were locally initiated.

ikeGlobalInitTunnelFails.name: ikeGlobalInitTunnelFails
ikeGlobalInitTunnelFails.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels which were locally initiated and failed to activate.

ikeGlobalRespTunnelFails.name: ikeGlobalRespTunnelFails
ikeGlobalRespTunnelFails.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels which were remotely initiated and failed to activate.

ikeGlobalSysCapFails.name: ikeGlobalSysCapFails
ikeGlobalSysCapFails.description: The total number of system capcity failures which occurred during processing of all current and previously active and ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalAuthFails.name: ikeGlobalAuthFails
ikeGlobalAuthFails.description: The total number of authentications which ended in failure by all current and previous ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalDecryptFails.name: ikeGlobalDecryptFails
ikeGlobalDecryptFails.description: The total number of decryptions which ended in failure by all current and previous ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalHashValidFails.name: ikeGlobalHashValidFails
ikeGlobalHashValidFails.description: The total number of hash validations which ended in failure by all current and previous ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikeGlobalNoSaFails.name: ikeGlobalNoSaFails
ikeGlobalNoSaFails.description: The total number of non-existent Security Assocication in failures which occurred during processing of all current and previous ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

ikePeerTable.name: ikePeerTable
ikePeerTable.description: The ipsec Phase-1 Internet Key Exchange Peer Table. There is one entry in this table for each ipsec Phase-1 IKE peer association which is currently associated with an active ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel. The ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel associated with this ipsec Phase-1 IKE peer association may or may not be currently active.

ikePeerEntry.name: ikePeerEntry
ikePeerEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an ipsec Phase-1 IKE peer association.

ikePeerLocalType.name: ikePeerLocalType
ikePeerLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity. The local peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

ikePeerLocalValue.name: ikePeerLocalValue
ikePeerLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity. If the local peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the local peer.

ikePeerRemoteType.name: ikePeerRemoteType
ikePeerRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer identity. The remote peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

ikePeerRemoteValue.name: ikePeerRemoteValue
ikePeerRemoteValue.description: The value of the remote peer identity. If the remote peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the remote peer. If the remote peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the remote peer.

ikePeerIntIndex.name: ikePeerIntIndex
ikePeerIntIndex.description: The internal index of the local-remote peer association. This internal index is used to uniquely identify multiple associations between the local and remote peer.

ikePeerLocalAddr.name: ikePeerLocalAddr
ikePeerLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local peer.

ikePeerRemoteAddr.name: ikePeerRemoteAddr
ikePeerRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote peer.

ikePeerActiveTime.name: ikePeerActiveTime
ikePeerActiveTime.description: The length of time that the peer association has existed in hundredths of a second.

ikePeerActiveTunnelIndex.name: ikePeerActiveTunnelIndex
ikePeerActiveTunnelIndex.description: The index of the active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (ikeTunIndex in the ikeTunnelTable) for this peer association. If an ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel is not currently active, then the value of this object will be zero.

ikeTunnelTable.name: ikeTunnelTable
ikeTunnelTable.description: The ipsec Phase-1 Internet Key Exchange Tunnel Table. There is one entry in this table for each active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunnelEntry.name: ikeTunnelEntry
ikeTunnelEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an active ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunIndex.name: ikeTunIndex
ikeTunIndex.description: The index of the ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that is created. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

ikeTunLocalType.name: ikeTunLocalType
ikeTunLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity. The local peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

ikeTunLocalValue.name: ikeTunLocalValue
ikeTunLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity. If the local peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the local peer.

ikeTunLocalAddr.name: ikeTunLocalAddr
ikeTunLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local endpoint for the ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunLocalName.name: ikeTunLocalName
ikeTunLocalName.description: The DNS name of the local IP address for the ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the local tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a NULL string.

ikeTunRemoteType.name: ikeTunRemoteType
ikeTunRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer identity. The remote peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

ikeTunRemoteValue.name: ikeTunRemoteValue
ikeTunRemoteValue.description: The value of the remote peer identity. If the remote peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the remote peer. If the remote peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the remote peer.

ikeTunRemoteAddr.name: ikeTunRemoteAddr
ikeTunRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote endpoint for the ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunRemoteName.name: ikeTunRemoteName
ikeTunRemoteName.description: The DNS name of the remote IP address of ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the remote tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a NULL string.

ikeTunNegoMode.name: ikeTunNegoMode
ikeTunNegoMode.description: The negotiation mode of the ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunDiffHellmanGrp.name: ikeTunDiffHellmanGrp
ikeTunDiffHellmanGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used in ipsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

ikeTunEncryptAlgo.name: ikeTunEncryptAlgo
ikeTunEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used in ipsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

ikeTunHashAlgo.name: ikeTunHashAlgo
ikeTunHashAlgo.description: The hash algorithm used in ipsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

ikeTunAuthMethod.name: ikeTunAuthMethod
ikeTunAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used in ipsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

ikeTunLifeTime.name: ikeTunLifeTime
ikeTunLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel in seconds.

ikeTunActiveTime.name: ikeTunActiveTime
ikeTunActiveTime.description: The length of time the ipsec Phase-1 IKE tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds.

ikeTunSaRefreshThreshold.name: ikeTunSaRefreshThreshold
ikeTunSaRefreshThreshold.description: The security assoication refresh threshold in seconds.

ikeTunTotalRefreshes.name: ikeTunTotalRefreshes
ikeTunTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security associations refreshes performed.

ikeTunInOctets.name: ikeTunInOctets
ikeTunInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunInPkts.name: ikeTunInPkts
ikeTunInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunInDropPkts.name: ikeTunInDropPkts
ikeTunInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel during receive processing.

ikeTunInNotifys.name: ikeTunInNotifys
ikeTunInNotifys.description: The total number of notifys received by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunInP2Exchgs.name: ikeTunInP2Exchgs
ikeTunInP2Exchgs.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges received by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunInP2ExchgInvalids.name: ikeTunInP2ExchgInvalids
ikeTunInP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges received and found to be invalid by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunInP2ExchgRejects.name: ikeTunInP2ExchgRejects
ikeTunInP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges received and rejected by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunInP2SaDelRequests.name: ikeTunInP2SaDelRequests
ikeTunInP2SaDelRequests.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 security association delete requests received by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunOutOctets.name: ikeTunOutOctets
ikeTunOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunOutPkts.name: ikeTunOutPkts
ikeTunOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunOutDropPkts.name: ikeTunOutDropPkts
ikeTunOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel during send processing.

ikeTunOutNotifys.name: ikeTunOutNotifys
ikeTunOutNotifys.description: The total number of notifys sent by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunOutP2Exchgs.name: ikeTunOutP2Exchgs
ikeTunOutP2Exchgs.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges sent by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunOutP2ExchgInvalids.name: ikeTunOutP2ExchgInvalids
ikeTunOutP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges sent and found to be invalid by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunOutP2ExchgRejects.name: ikeTunOutP2ExchgRejects
ikeTunOutP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 exchanges sent and rejected by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunOutP2SaDelRequests.name: ikeTunOutP2SaDelRequests
ikeTunOutP2SaDelRequests.description: The total number of ipsec Phase-2 security association delete requests sent by this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunStatus.name: ikeTunStatus
ikeTunStatus.description: The status of the MIB table row. This object can be used to bring the tunnel down by setting value of this object to destroy(2). This object cannot be used to create a MIB table row.

ikePeerCorrTable.name: ikePeerCorrTable
ikePeerCorrTable.description: The ipsec Phase-1 Internet Key Exchange Peer Association to ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel Correlation Table. There is one entry in this table for each active ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ikePeerCorrEntry.name: ikePeerCorrEntry
ikePeerCorrEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes of an an ipsec Phase-1 IKE Peer Association to ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel Correlation.

ikePeerCorrLocalType.name: ikePeerCorrLocalType
ikePeerCorrLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity. The local peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

ikePeerCorrLocalValue.name: ikePeerCorrLocalValue
ikePeerCorrLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity. If the local peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the local peer.

ikePeerCorrRemoteType.name: ikePeerCorrRemoteType
ikePeerCorrRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer identity. The remote peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. a host name.

ikePeerCorrRemoteValue.name: ikePeerCorrRemoteValue
ikePeerCorrRemoteValue.description: The value of the remote peer identity. If the remote peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the remote peer. If the remote peer type is a host name, then this is the host name used to identify the remote peer.

ikePeerCorrIntIndex.name: ikePeerCorrIntIndex
ikePeerCorrIntIndex.description: The internal index of the local-remote peer association. This internal index is used to uniquely identify multiple associations between the local and remote peer.

ikePeerCorrSeqNum.name: ikePeerCorrSeqNum
ikePeerCorrSeqNum.description: The sequence number of the local-remote peer association. This sequence number is used to uniquely identify multiple instances of an unique association between the local and remote peer.

ikePeerCorripsecTunIndex.name: ikePeerCorripsecTunIndex
ikePeerCorripsecTunIndex.description: The index of the active ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel (ipsecTunIndex in the ipsecTunnelTable) for this ipsec Phase-1 IKE Peer Association.

ipsecGlobalActiveTunnels.name: ipsecGlobalActiveTunnels
ipsecGlobalActiveTunnels.description: The total number of currently active ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalPreviousTunnels.name: ipsecGlobalPreviousTunnels
ipsecGlobalPreviousTunnels.description: The total number of previously active ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalInOctets.name: ipsecGlobalInOctets
ipsecGlobalInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed. See also ipsecGlobalInOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

ipsecGlobalHcInOctets.name: ipsecGlobalHcInOctets
ipsecGlobalHcInOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets received by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

ipsecGlobalInOctWraps.name: ipsecGlobalInOctWraps
ipsecGlobalInOctWraps.description: The number of times the global octets received counter (ipsecGlobalInOctets) has wrapped.

ipsecGlobalInDecompOctets.name: ipsecGlobalInDecompOctets
ipsecGlobalInDecompOctets.description: The total number of decompressed octets received by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ipsecGlobalInOctets. See also ipsecGlobalInDecompOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

ipsecGlobalHcInDecompOctets.name: ipsecGlobalHcInDecompOctets
ipsecGlobalHcInDecompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of decompressed octets received by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ipsecGlobalHcInOctets.

ipsecGlobalInDecompOctWraps.name: ipsecGlobalInDecompOctWraps
ipsecGlobalInDecompOctWraps.description: The number of times the global decompressed octets received counter (ipsecGlobalInDecompOctets) has wrapped.

ipsecGlobalInPkts.name: ipsecGlobalInPkts
ipsecGlobalInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalInDrops.name: ipsecGlobalInDrops
ipsecGlobalInDrops.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This count does NOT include packets dropped due to Anti-Replay processing.

ipsecGlobalInReplayDrops.name: ipsecGlobalInReplayDrops
ipsecGlobalInReplayDrops.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing due to Anti-Replay processing by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalInAuths.name: ipsecGlobalInAuths
ipsecGlobalInAuths.description: The total number of inbound authentication's performed by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalInAuthFails.name: ipsecGlobalInAuthFails
ipsecGlobalInAuthFails.description: The total number of inbound authentication's which ended in failure by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalInDecrypts.name: ipsecGlobalInDecrypts
ipsecGlobalInDecrypts.description: The total number of inbound decryption's performed by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalInDecryptFails.name: ipsecGlobalInDecryptFails
ipsecGlobalInDecryptFails.description: The total number of inbound decryption's which ended in failure by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalOutOctets.name: ipsecGlobalOutOctets
ipsecGlobalOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed. See also ipsecGlobalOutOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

ipsecGlobalHcOutOctets.name: ipsecGlobalHcOutOctets
ipsecGlobalHcOutOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets sent by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

ipsecGlobalOutOctWraps.name: ipsecGlobalOutOctWraps
ipsecGlobalOutOctWraps.description: The number of times the global octets sent counter (ipsecGlobalOutOctets) has wrapped.

ipsecGlobalOutUncompOctets.name: ipsecGlobalOutUncompOctets
ipsecGlobalOutUncompOctets.description: The total number of uncompressed octets sent by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ipsecGlobalOutOctets. See also ipsecGlobalOutDecompOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

ipsecGlobalHcOutUncompOctets.name: ipsecGlobalHcOutUncompOctets
ipsecGlobalHcOutUncompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of uncompressed octets sent by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ipsecGlobalHcOutOctets.

ipsecGlobalOutUncompOctWraps.name: ipsecGlobalOutUncompOctWraps
ipsecGlobalOutUncompOctWraps.description: The number of times the global uncompressed octets sent counter (ipsecGlobalInUncompOctets) has wrapped.

ipsecGlobalOutPkts.name: ipsecGlobalOutPkts
ipsecGlobalOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalOutDrops.name: ipsecGlobalOutDrops
ipsecGlobalOutDrops.description: The total number of packets dropped during send processing by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalOutAuths.name: ipsecGlobalOutAuths
ipsecGlobalOutAuths.description: The total number of outbound authentication's performed by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalOutAuthFails.name: ipsecGlobalOutAuthFails
ipsecGlobalOutAuthFails.description: The total number of outbound authentication's which ended in failure by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalOutEncrypts.name: ipsecGlobalOutEncrypts
ipsecGlobalOutEncrypts.description: The total number of outbound encryption's performed by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalOutEncryptFails.name: ipsecGlobalOutEncryptFails
ipsecGlobalOutEncryptFails.description: The total number of outbound encryption's which ended in failure by all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalProtocolUseFails.name: ipsecGlobalProtocolUseFails
ipsecGlobalProtocolUseFails.description: The total number of protocol use failures which occurred during processing of all current and previously active and ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalNoSaFails.name: ipsecGlobalNoSaFails
ipsecGlobalNoSaFails.description: The total number of non-existent Security Assocication in failures which occurred during processing of all current and previous ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecGlobalSysCapFails.name: ipsecGlobalSysCapFails
ipsecGlobalSysCapFails.description: The total number of system capcity failures which occurred during processing of all current and previously active and ipsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ipsecTunnelTable.name: ipsecTunnelTable
ipsecTunnelTable.description: The ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. There is one entry in this table for each active ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipsecTunnelEntry.name: ipsecTunnelEntry
ipsecTunnelEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an active ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipsecTunIndex.name: ipsecTunIndex
ipsecTunIndex.description: The index of the ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that is created. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

ipsecTunIkeTunnelIndex.name: ipsecTunIkeTunnelIndex
ipsecTunIkeTunnelIndex.description: The index of the associated ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel. (ikeTunIndex in the ikeTunnelTable)

ipsecTunIkeTunnelAlive.name: ipsecTunIkeTunnelAlive
ipsecTunIkeTunnelAlive.description: An indicator which specifies whether or not the ipsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel currently exists.

ipsecTunLocalAddr.name: ipsecTunLocalAddr
ipsecTunLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local endpoint for the ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipsecTunRemoteAddr.name: ipsecTunRemoteAddr
ipsecTunRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote endpoint for the ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipsecTunKeyType.name: ipsecTunKeyType
ipsecTunKeyType.description: The type of key used by the ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipsecTunEncapMode.name: ipsecTunEncapMode
ipsecTunEncapMode.description: The encapsulation mode used by the ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipsecTunLifeSize.name: ipsecTunLifeSize
ipsecTunLifeSize.description: The negotiated LifeSize of the ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel in kilobytes.

ipsecTunLifeTime.name: ipsecTunLifeTime
ipsecTunLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel in seconds.

ipsecTunActiveTime.name: ipsecTunActiveTime
ipsecTunActiveTime.description: The length of time the ipsec Phase-2 Tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds.

ipsecTunSaLifeSizeThreshold.name: ipsecTunSaLifeSizeThreshold
